Pokédoro Timer

A Pokémon-themed Pomodoro productivity app that combines focused productivity sessions with fun, game-like rewards.
Users complete timed work sessions to encounter and catch Pokémon, track their collection in a Pokédex, and manage 
tasks with a built-in to-do list.

Features

Pomodoro & Break Timer
- Study and break timers, with start, pause, resume and reset functionality
- Automatic break session after completing a study timer
- Real-time countdown updates

Pokemon Encounter (API Integration)
- Random Pokémon encounters provided by the PokeAPI
- Shiny Pokémon chance system
- Catch or release Pokémon at the end of each study session

Pokédex
- Stores caught Pokémon using localStorage
- Displays Pokémon sprites, names, and shiny status
- Filter Pokémon by type
- Remove individual Pokémon or clear the entire Pokédex

To-Do List
- Add, check off, and remove tasks
- Persistent storage using localStorage
- Keyboard accessibility (Enter key support)

Live Date & Time
- Displays the current date and time
- Automatically updates every second


Technologies Used
- HTML5 – Semantic page structure
- CSS3 – Flexbox, Grid, custom fonts, responsive layout
- JavaScript (ES6+) – Application logic, timers, DOM manipulation
- PokéAPI – External API for Pokémon data
- Local Storage API – Persistent user data storage


Responsive Design
- Uses CSS Grid and Flexbox for layout
- Responsive adjustments for desktop and mobile screens via media queries
- Optimized for usability across different screen sizes

